# Web security (mandatory)

Read [SECURITY.md](../../SECURITY.md) and [docs/security/web-security-rules.md](../../docs/security/web-security-rules.md) before auth, billing, Supabase, API routes, server actions, AI, or env changes.

## Browser is untrusted

Never treat client state, storage, bundles, network responses, or `NEXT_PUBLIC_*` as authoritative for identity, subscription, verification, entitlements, AI limits, admin, deletion, or ownership.

## Secrets

- Never put secrets in client code or `NEXT_PUBLIC_*`.
- Never commit service role keys, DB passwords, RevenueCat/OpenAI/webhook secrets, admin tokens.
- Allowed public env only: `NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL`, `NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY`, `NEXT_PUBLIC_SITE_URL`, `NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_ENV`.

## No raw backend truth in the client

Do not add or return raw fields like `isVerified`, `hasActiveSubscription`, `isAdmin`, `entitlementStatus`, `subscriptionExpiresAt`, `revenueCatCustomerId`, AI limit counters, `deletedAt`, raw entitlement/billing rows.

Use sanitized display DTOs (e.g. `canUseAi`, `canExportPdf`, `planLabel`) for UI only. Re-check access server-side on every protected action.

## Data access pattern (Next.js)

```
Client → Server Action/API/Server Component → server-only module (import 'server-only') → Supabase/Edge → sanitized DTO → client
```

Forbidden: Client Component → privileged query → raw row → client decides access.

No `"use client"` file may import server-only env/config/data modules.

## Supabase

- Wire Supabase only when explicitly requested.
- Every user-owned table: RLS on before production; policies use `auth.uid()` (e.g. `user_id = auth.uid()` or `id = auth.uid()` for profiles).
- Never rely on client-side filtering as security.

## Entitlements and AI

- Subscription truth: App Store/RevenueCat → webhook → Supabase mirror → server/Edge → optional sanitized DTO.
- Hiding UI is not protection; gate AI, export, premium features on the server at action time.
- No LLM calls from the browser; keys server-only; suggestions only, user-approved, no auto-overwrite of CV.
- Do not log raw prompts, responses, or full CV/job text by default.

## API / ownership / XSS

- Auth + authorize + Zod validate + prove ownership; minimal responses; no mutation via GET; CSRF if cookie auth.
- Never trust `resumeId` / `jobId` / `userId` from URL or body without server ownership proof.
- User content untrusted: text by default; no `dangerouslySetInnerHTML` without strict sanitization; validate URLs.

## CV data

- `resume_json` sensitive; full JSON only where needed (builder/export/scoped AI). Not in dashboards, analytics, or logs.
- No exported PDF storage in Supabase v1 unless requested.

## Privacy and deps

- No analytics/tracking/cookies/third-party scripts without explicit instruction and documentation (CSP, privacy).
- No privacy claims in UI that are not implemented.
- Before new deps: client exposure, telemetry, CSP impact, necessity.

## PRs touching auth/data/AI/billing/env

Confirm: no client secrets; no raw rows to client; RLS; server-side ownership and entitlement checks; validated inputs; no GET mutations; redacted logs; documented third parties.

When `50-security-backend.mdc` and this file differ on security posture, follow this file and SECURITY.md.
